This article is a message from the White House Office of the Press Secretary, dated May 16, 2012. It states that the President has issued an Executive Order declaring a national emergency with respect to the threat posed by certain members of the Government of Yemen and others to Yemen's peace, security, and stability. The order targets individuals who obstruct the implementation of a peaceful transition of power in Yemen or obstruct the political process in the country. The Secretary of the Treasury, in consultation with the Secretary of State, has been given the authority to block the property and interests in property of individuals who meet certain criteria outlined in the order. The order also delegates the authority to take necessary actions to carry out the order's purposes to the Secretary of the Treasury. All U.S. government agencies are directed to take appropriate measures to enforce the provisions of the order.